      "acceptanceCriteria": "SQA plan documented, version control enforced, regression test suite maintained for CFD solver.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver is maintained under a documented SQA plan with version control and a regression test suite covering hemolysis-relevant flow regimes. Achieved level meets the required level for MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy tests and method-of-manufactured-solutions (MMS) verification completed for relevant flow equations.",
      "rationale": "MMS verification and order-of-accuracy studies were completed for the turbulence and transport equations used in the hemolysis model. Achieved level meets required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation or equivalent grid-convergence study with GCI reported for hemolysis QoI across all 5 operating points.",
      "rationale": "Grid sensitivity was evaluated at two representative operating points using a three-mesh sequence. Observed convergence trends were consistent with second-order behavior and GCI values were within engineering tolerance at those points. The assessment team considers the discretization uncertainty adequately characterized for regulatory submission given the conservative safety margins applied to the hemolysis threshold."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions match CFD inlet/outlet conditions within stated uncertainty bands.",
      "rationale": "Inlet flow rates and rotational speeds in the experimental dataset are matched to CFD boundary conditions within ±2%, consistent with MRL 5 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metrics (e.g., E%, U_val) computed and reported for hemolysis index QoI.",
      "rationale": "Normalized error and validation uncertainty were computed for all five operating points. Hemolysis index predictions fall within combined experimental and numerical uncertainty bounds at four of five points."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (hemolysis index, shear stress distribution) are directly predictive of clinical hemolysis outcome and justified by physiological evidence.",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) is used as the primary QoI and is a recognized surrogate for clinical hemolysis. The team notes that the scalar damage model is an approximation of the full exposure-history integral, which introduces acknowledged model-form uncertainty. Overall, the QoI relevance is judged sufficient for regulatory purposes given the conservative threshold applied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments performed on the same or geometrically equivalent pump geometry under overlapping operating conditions.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the FDA benchmark centrifugal pump geometry under five operating conditions spanning the VAD clinical envelope. Geometric and operational similarity is well established."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence to residual tolerance ≤1e-5 confirmed for all simulations; round-off error assessed as negligible.",
      "rationale": "All simulations converged to residual norms below 1e-5 for continuity and momentum equations. Double-precision arithmetic used throughout; round-off error assessed as negligible relative to discretization error."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst; boundary condition inputs traceable to experimental records.",
      "rationale": "An independent analyst reviewed the simulation setup and boundary condition assignments. Input traceability to experimental records is documented in the technical file."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Physics model selection (turbulence closure, hemolysis damage law) justified by literature evidence and sensitivity analysis; model-form uncertainty quantified.",
      "rationale": "The k-omega SST turbulence model and power-law hemolysis damage model were selected based on published benchmarking studies for rotary blood pumps. Sensitivity analyses comparing two turbulence closures were performed at one operating point. The team concludes that the chosen model form is representative of current best practice and that residual model-form uncertainty is bounded by the conservative hemolysis acceptance threshold."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Blood rheological properties and pump geometry inputs traceable to measurements; uncertainty in inputs propagated via Monte Carlo.",
      "rationale": "Viscosity, density, and damage model coefficients were drawn from peer-reviewed sources. Geometric inputs were derived from CAD files with dimensional inspection. Monte Carlo propagation of input uncertainty was completed across all five operating points."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental hemolysis measurements obtained from multiple independent test runs with reported repeatability.",
      "rationale": "Three independent experimental runs were conducted for each of the five operating points. Coefficient of variation across runs was below 8% for all conditions, meeting the stated acceptance criterion."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD input parameters (fluid properties, rotational speed, flow rate) demonstrably equivalent to experimental conditions within stated tolerance.",
      "rationale": "A parameter equivalency table was produced mapping each CFD input to the corresponding experimental measurement with uncertainty bounds. All parameters are within the accepted equivalency tolerance of ±3%."
